Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.83,0:00:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}The dreams embraced by a single life{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.84,0:00:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}are boundless beyond even the stars.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.84,0:00:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}The dreams that we foster over time{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.85,0:00:40.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}are waiting for the moment{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}when we come upon them.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.53,0:00:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}The words we exchange{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}make our hearts tremble,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.53,0:00:52.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}and a chance meeting{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}could change the future.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.21,0:01:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}People, no matter who they are,{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}as they pursue their dreams,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.48,0:01:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}have the courage to travel new paths.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.15,0:01:15.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}As we leave behind a living{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}testament of our journey,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.49,0:01:25.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}the Galaxy Railways on which{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}we travel continue ever on.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.19,0:01:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Planet Haaga Loo,{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}a world bound by snow and ice.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.53,0:01:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}It is said that somewhere on this planet{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.46,0:01:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}lies the most beautiful jewel{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}in the universe.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.14,0:02:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Many treasure hunters{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}have visited this planet,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.78,0:02:10.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}hoping to obtain this jewel...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.49,0:02:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}But none have ever returned.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.72,0:02:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}"Armored Goddess"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.16,0:02:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Receiving a message\N{\c&He1e1e1&}from Tovulcan Station.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.50,0:02:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}An unidentified small craft has crashed\N{\c&He1e1e1&}on the tracks ten kilos away from us.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.50,0:02:33.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Acknowledged. Let's head to the site.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.85,0:03:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Hey, wake up!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.18,0:03:57.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.19,0:04:00.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Irene?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.13,0:04:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Where am I?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.13,0:04:17.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You have been rescued by the SDF...\N{\c&He1e1e1&}the Space Defense Force.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.81,0:04:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Your life is no longer in danger,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}so please do not worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.81,0:04:23.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's been a long time, Irene.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.81,0:04:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}David!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.81,0:04:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.15,0:04:30.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Y- yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.15,0:04:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You came all the way out here\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to find some treasure?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.82,0:04:38.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}So pretty... you haven't changed at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.83,0:04:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Well, you take it easy, now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.17,0:04:51.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It looks like the small craft\N{\c&He1e1e1&}was headed for that canyon
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.41,0:04:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}when it got into an accident and crashed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.84,0:04:57.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}There is a record in the flight recorder\N{\c&He1e1e1&}of what happened just before the crash.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.21,0:04:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.85,0:05:03.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Something just showed up there.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Please let me see it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.45,0:05:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The residents of this planet\N{\c&He1e1e1&}observe an archaic way of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.59,0:05:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That could be a vigilante.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.13,0:05:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Planet Haaga Loo here has\N{\c&He1e1e1&}a smattering of ancient ruins,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.80,0:05:20.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}and the Galaxy Railways Headquarters\N{\c&He1e1e1&}has made it a class one preservation zone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.47,0:05:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}However, there are a lot of people\N{\c&He1e1e1&}that come here for other reasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.14,0:05:25.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Are there any treasures here?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.47,0:05:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This canyon is called\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Annuvun's Cauldron.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.48,0:05:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It is believed that\N{\c&He1e1e1&}the Blue Flame of Isperil,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.71,0:05:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}said to be the most beautiful jewel in\N{\c&He1e1e1&}the universe, is around here somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.15,0:05:37.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The Blue Flame of Isperil?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.15,0:05:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}If you possess it, your beauty will\N{\c&He1e1e1&}never fade. At least, that's the story.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.16,0:05:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}David...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.16,0:05:45.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Let him be.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.16,0:05:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Now that she's in our custody,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.26,0:05:49.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}we don't have much choice\N{\c&He1e1e1&}but to take her back with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.16,0:05:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The folks at headquarters\N{\c&He1e1e1&}will probably question her.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.78,0:06:04.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.45,0:06:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}First time we see each other\N{\c&He1e1e1&}in seven years,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.11,0:06:07.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}and you're not even going to say goodbye?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.78,0:06:10.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Let go of me! I've got nothing\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to do with you anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.79,0:06:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Have you forgotten? That's too bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.15,0:06:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I haven't gotten my\N{\c&He1e1e1&}1 million ables from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.13,0:06:19.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}David...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.79,0:06:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm sorry. I feel terrible about it.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}I needed the money really bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.13,0:06:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Not a day goes by that\N{\c&He1e1e1&}I don't think about you...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.80,0:06:30.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}David, I love you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.48,0:06:37.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}So forget about me!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.15,0:06:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.49,0:06:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You let her go? You gave up\N{\c&He1e1e1&}pretty quickly, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.82,0:06:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I've been waiting for seven years.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.63,0:06:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm not about to let her\N{\c&He1e1e1&}get away so easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.83,0:07:00.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}So, should we bet on it? A million ables\N{\c&He1e1e1&}says I'm able to get Irene.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.77,0:07:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Listen to you! Go catch yourself a cold!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.81,0:07:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}That was the guardian of the jewel...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.82,0:07:56.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Help! Please! Somebody!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.83,0:08:02.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Please! Somebody, open up!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.43,0:08:04.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Help!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.11,0:08:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Thanks! You saved...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.45,0:08:24.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Treasure hunter, if you value\N{\c&He1e1e1&}your life, you'll come with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.12,0:08:30.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'll just express my gratitude.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Thanks for saving me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.47,0:08:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Manabu, you were\N{\c&He1e1e1&}spying on us earlier, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.14,0:08:43.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Sorry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.47,0:08:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}She is Irene Summer.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.51,0:08:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Seven years ago, she's the woman\N{\c&He1e1e1&}who disappeared with my 1 million ables.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.14,0:08:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I knew she wasn't just anyone!\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Reunited after seven years... how romantic!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.72,0:08:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Irene-san{\i0} was your girlfriend, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.82,0:08:59.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Whoa, Louis!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.15,0:09:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Ah, that's okay. I wouldn't\N{\c&He1e1e1&}ask you to share your painful past.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.42,0:09:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I bet a lot happened, though. How neat!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.13,0:09:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'd like to have an affair\N{\c&He1e1e1&}with that kind of suspense, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.76,0:09:14.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Hey, David, {\i1}Louis-chan{\i0} wants to hear\N{\c&He1e1e1&}stories about your torrid love affair.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.77,0:09:16.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Drop it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.44,0:09:19.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}David, you're being unusually demure!\N{\c&He1e1e1&}How adorable!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.80,0:09:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Morgana-sama,{\i0} how was today's hunt?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.47,0:09:54.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I only caught four rats.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Not even enough to feed the Mach Crows.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.15,0:10:03.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This is an incredible castle. I wonder\N{\c&He1e1e1&}what sort of king must live here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.15,0:10:06.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}At this hour, I doubt\N{\c&He1e1e1&}we'll be invited in.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.49,0:10:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Are you sure she fled here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.82,0:10:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yeah, no doubt about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.49,0:10:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What business do you have\N{\c&He1e1e1&}at Gusfantail Castle?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.50,0:10:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We're with the SDF. We believe that\N{\c&He1e1e1&}someone who was marooned here fled inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.51,0:10:32.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I am Kinderick, Head Knight\N{\c&He1e1e1&}of Gusfantail Castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.35,0:10:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You should ask Lady {\i1}Morgana-sama{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&}about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.18,0:10:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This way.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.19,0:10:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Wait here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.86,0:10:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Forlorn travelers,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}camest ye to this accursed castle...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.86,0:10:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}...for to be its prisoners?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.53,0:10:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The Blue Flame of Isperil\N{\c&He1e1e1&}hath an unholy life.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.30,0:10:54.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}If thou adornest thyself with it,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}thou wilt become the jewel's slave.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.87,0:10:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Travelers, take ye heed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.20,0:11:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}All those who draw nigh unto the jewel\N{\c&He1e1e1&}falleth prey to its evil presence.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.48,0:11:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Voyagers of the heavens,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}welcome to my castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.50,0:11:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Treasure hunter, have you come here\N{\c&He1e1e1&}for the Blue Flame of Isperil, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.51,0:11:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}All of your comrades are dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.35,0:11:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Right now, the Mach Crows\N{\c&He1e1e1&}are probably devouring their souls.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.85,0:11:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You're a brave woman.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Do you want eternal life?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.19,0:11:50.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Its glow smolders as a blue flame,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.79,0:11:55.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}and it is said that those who wear it\N{\c&He1e1e1&}are given eternal life and beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.53,0:12:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Why have you decided to let me have it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.80,0:12:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Why, indeed... If you want it,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}descend into Annuvun's Cauldron.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.14,0:12:10.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}If you go down this hallway, you will\N{\c&He1e1e1&}come out at the bottom of the Cauldron.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.82,0:12:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}So, you're searching for\N{\c&He1e1e1&}this woman named Irene?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.15,0:12:24.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That's right. Irene was chased\N{\c&He1e1e1&}by a group on horseback.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.39,0:12:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Morgana-san,{\i0} you wouldn't be\N{\c&He1e1e1&}hiding anything from us, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.26,0:12:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We followed her signal here. That signal\N{\c&He1e1e1&}has stopped moving inside this castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.84,0:12:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We're asking you to\N{\c&He1e1e1&}allow us to check it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.51,0:12:41.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I know nothing about it.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Please leave now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.18,0:12:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Bruce!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.51,0:12:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.85,0:12:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Irene has started moving.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.19,0:12:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Oh, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.80,0:13:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Could the jewel really be down this way?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.14,0:13:18.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Morgana-sama...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.81,0:13:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I can't bear to take any more lives!\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Kinderick, bind this accursed body!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.12,0:13:25.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}No, kill it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.49,0:13:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Morgana-sama,{\i0} please listen to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.89,0:13:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}There is a way to\N{\c&He1e1e1&}change your cursed fate.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.83,0:13:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Change my fate?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.83,0:13:37.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Morgana-sama,{\i0} you are\N{\c&He1e1e1&}possessed by that jewel.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.50,0:13:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}If the jewel were to\N{\c&He1e1e1&}obtain a new sacrifice,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.30,0:13:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}you should be released.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.84,0:13:46.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}But how? I cannot remove it.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}When I become the Black Knight,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.57,0:13:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I mercilessly take\N{\c&He1e1e1&}people's lives from them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.18,0:13:53.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Nonetheless, that is the only way.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.13,0:14:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Go, {\i1}Morgana-sama,{\i0} to the sealing altar\N{\c&He1e1e1&}at the bottom of Annuvun's Cauldron.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.82,0:14:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Looks like I'm going down.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.16,0:14:40.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Just a moment. You are going to the\N{\c&He1e1e1&}bottom of Annuvun's Cauldron, yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.83,0:14:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm just going after Irene.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm not interested in the jewel.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.17,0:14:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The Blue Flame of Isperil\N{\c&He1e1e1&}is a cursed jewel.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.10,0:14:51.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Mankind must not take it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.17,0:14:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That which God hath created\N{\c&He1e1e1&}is for the hand of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.84,0:14:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That which transcendeth time\N{\c&He1e1e1&}is for days of yore.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.12,0:15:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Irene!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.12,0:15:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}David!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.46,0:15:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}There's something I forgot to tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.13,0:15:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Are you trying to catch me?\N{\c&He1e1e1&}That's a shame.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.80,0:15:16.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Irene!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.13,0:15:20.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Where are we?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.47,0:15:21.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.80,0:15:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's almost like we're in another world.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.80,0:15:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That's strange. We're beneath the castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.48,0:15:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I can't get through.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}What the hell is going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.15,0:15:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Who cares? All I want to know\N{\c&He1e1e1&}is where the Blue Flame is.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.16,0:15:46.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Damn!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.83,0:15:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}David's signal has disappeared\N{\c&He1e1e1&}from the spatial radar.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.83,0:15:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We should contact\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Captain Bulge immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.83,0:15:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}No, he's no klutz. Let's wait a\N{\c&He1e1e1&}little longer for him to contact us.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.78,0:16:11.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.79,0:16:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The Blue Flame of Isperil.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.12,0:16:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We're watching something\N{\c&He1e1e1&}that happened here in the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.82,0:16:48.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Watch out!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.44,0:17:04.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Irene, run!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.44,0:17:09.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.45,0:17:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}David!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.12,0:17:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You coward! And you\N{\c&He1e1e1&}call yourself a knight!?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.45,0:17:21.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Why do you vex me?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.79,0:17:28.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I am a slave to the jewel. I cannot\N{\c&He1e1e1&}stay my sword any longer! Go, now!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.13,0:17:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}No way! I'll get that jewel from you,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.36,0:17:31.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}if only just to see this\N{\c&He1e1e1&}through to the end!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.47,0:17:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Hurry! Go!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.15,0:17:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You must not put it on!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.49,0:17:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Hold on!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.82,0:18:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Do you want life eternal?\N{\c&He1e1e1&}You don't do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.16,0:18:03.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Stay out of this. This jewel is mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.43,0:18:05.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Irene, open your eyes!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.77,0:18:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}No!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.11,0:18:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That which God hath created\N{\c&He1e1e1&}is for the hand of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.78,0:18:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That which transcendeth time\N{\c&He1e1e1&}is for days of yore.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.79,0:18:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.46,0:18:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Your love has overcome the jewel's curse.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.80,0:18:40.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Farewell. We shall not meet again.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.82,0:19:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}They're gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.76,0:19:04.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}So, what was it you forgot to tell me?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.09,0:19:06.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I lent you a million ables, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.43,0:19:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You dummy. You came all\N{\c&He1e1e1&}this way to tell me that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.12,0:19:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What the hell happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.79,0:19:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Search me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.46,0:19:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Anyhow, I'm glad you're all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.13,0:19:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}So what was Gusfantail Castle, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.80,0:19:52.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Some wandering spirits must have needed\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to tell their sad story to somebody.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.47,0:19:55.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Heh, what are you acting so\N{\c&He1e1e1&}pretentious for? Let's go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.81,0:19:58.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}The jewel has fallen asleep.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.81,0:20:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}However, mankind's greed knows no bound.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.15,0:20:08.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Someday, someone may come along{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}and reawaken the legend.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.49,0:20:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We rescued the marooned woman.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Each member of Sirius Platoon
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.59,0:20:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}carried out their duties\N{\c&He1e1e1&}and accomplished their mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.16,0:20:15.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Let's report it like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.83,0:20:18.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You sure had us hopping around.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.17,0:20:20.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Okay then, prepare for departure.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.83,0:20:22.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}- Roger.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}- Roger.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}- Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.85,0:20:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yuki, do you know what happened to Irene?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.19,0:20:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Irene already left.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.19,0:20:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This is from her.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.87,0:20:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}I'm sorry, David. I didn't have{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}the courage to tell you goodbye.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.54,0:20:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}But I will come back to{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}see you again someday for sure.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.64,0:21:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}After all, you are someone{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}dear to me, even now.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.82,0:21:11.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}A thousand ables, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.15,0:21:14.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}999,000 ables to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.49,0:21:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Irene, we'll meet again.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.18,0:21:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}How many nights have I\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}spent alone since then?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.19,0:22:09.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Constantly having dreams of the hope{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}that you are, as I lightly sleep.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.87,0:22:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}The smiles and tears{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}that you gave to me and me alone{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.88,0:22:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}come to mind every time{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}I get disheartened,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.22,0:22:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}and I set forth again toward the morrow.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.89,0:22:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}The joyful light of the galaxy beckons me{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.50,0:22:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}to that beloved person within my heart.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.51,0:22:54.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}No matter how far apart we are,{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}my memories will never fade.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.18,0:23:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}My heart wishes always{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}to be at your side.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.20,0:23:19.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}An intruder at SDF Headquarters...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.54,0:23:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}The flickering image{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}of the Grim Reaper...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.54,0:23:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Do I have to go through{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}that tragedy again?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.55,0:23:29.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Next time on Tales of the{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Galaxy Railways, Episode 18:{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&}"Life or Death"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.88,0:23:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}We're going to encounter{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}something at the next station.{\i0}